SIMPLE: efferent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Efferent
<hw>Ef"fe*rent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>efferens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>effere</ets> to
bear out; <ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>ferre</ets> to bear.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Conveying outward, or
discharging; -- applied to certain blood vessels, lymphatics, nerves,
etc.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Conveyed outward; <as>as, <ex>efferent</ex>
impulses, <it>i. e.</it>, such as are conveyed by the motor or
<ex>efferent</ex> nerves from the central nervous organ outwards</as>;
-- opposed to <contr>afferent</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Efferent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Efferent
<hw>Ef"fe*rent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An efferent duct or
stream.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Efferous</ent>⟦br⟧
